  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Thousands of coastal residents from Mexico to Louisiana fled to higher ground Thursday 09/15/1988 as fierce Hurricane Gilbert sent the first of its storms against Texas after thrashing the Yucatan Peninsula.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The weather service issued a hurricane warning for Mexico's northern coast and the southern half of the 370-mile Texas coast from Brownsville to Port O'Connor.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   A hurricane watch remained in effect for the remainder of the Texas coast, from Port O'Connor north to Port Arthur near the Louisiana border.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The weather service said warnings might be extended northward, depending on the path of the 450-mile wide storm.
  </a>
